owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: This ontology was created by Davide Apolloni for his masters' thesis on digital curation. The supervisor is Simona Caraceni, professor at University of Bologna and active member of Cineca Visit Lab. The co-supervisor is Silvano Imboden, computer scientist and expert on 3D graphics at Cineca Visit Lab.

This ontology was created to provide a framework aimed at sustaining digital preservation practices. Starting from a main repository, which is usually a dedicated external hard drive where files are stored, classes, object properties and data properties will help to define the relationships and dependances among the various files that are contained. The properties represent a basic starting point to take care of digital objects and their long-term preservations. As a matter of fact, adding the kind of information which is presented here is fundamental to ensure a better understanding and a more durable life to the digital objects.

To provide a real-life implementation, the digital curation activity has been carried out here on the first of the three hard disks storing all the digital objects produced by Cineca Visit Lab, the 3D graphic laboratory located in Casalecchio di Reno (BO). The ontology will be implemented even on the other two hard disks, to ensure a better preservation to the files, other than testifying how a framework can be used and adapted even when the involved files are different. The final result shows an innovative way to take care of digital objects in order to assure them long-term preservation over years.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A folder, or a file, usually belongs to a main one, which is their father.
A folder can contain single files.
A folder can contain other folders containing other folders or elements.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: This property allows to write a brief description of the file or folder, taking into consideration its contents and history.
This property allows to define the format of the file.
This property allows to define the type of the file, which is different than the format. A file type can simply be a directory, for example, whereas the format requires to state the file extension.
A folder contains files of various formats. This properties allows to define them and write them as a string.
This property allows to describe the size that the file occupies.
This property allows to define how elements are organized inside a bigger folder.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A very important step when performing the digital curation of objects concerns the division of them over the years. This action can be done both by the institution or by the digital curator.

A digital curator should be able to identify macroareas where common objects can be stored. Finding macroareas makes the work of the digital curator faster, easier and definitely more accurate. It also gives the opportunity to produce a more organized set of files that the institution can benefit from.

The main repository is usually an external hard drive where the institution stored its files. However, it might be even a computer or other storage devices, if the institution decided to adopt a different approach.
Single files might be found, and if they appear to be too important to be removed, they must be classified as such.
Instead each backup folder there might be sub and sub-subfolders. It is very important to avoid having extremely long file paths.
